\fs28 \cf0 \
\'a5 Launch it\
\'a5 Select File->Open to open any QuickTime supported image file, or alternately select File->Open Digital Camera Image to acquire an image from any connected digital camera (only the first image found in the camera is used)\
\'a5 Using the profile popups in the Image Profile window, select any desired source, abstract, proofer or destination profiles\
\'a5 A ColorSync color world is automatically created for the selected profiles, the image is color matched using this color world and the resulting color-matched image is displayed in the window\
\'a5 Repeat as necessary\
\'a5 Alternately, on Panther systems select "Use Panther QuickTime ColorSync matching" in the Image Profiles window. This causes the image to be automatically color matched using the QuickTime Graphics Importer components. The QuickTime Graphics Importer ColorSync support in Panther makes use of any profile embedded in the image, and allows the user to override both this embedded source profile and the destination profile.\
